{"title_page": "Savage (song)", "text_new": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = Savage\n| type       = single\n| cover      = Megan Thee Stallion featuring Major Lazer - Savage (Remix).png\n| caption    = [[Major Lazer]] remix artwork\n| alt        =\n| artist     = [[Megan Thee Stallion]]\n| EP         = [[Suga (EP)|Suga]]\n| released   = April 7, 2020\n| format     =\n* [[Music download|Digital download]]\n* [[Streaming media|streaming]]\n| recorded   =\n| genre      = \n| length     = {{duration|m=2|s=35}}\n| label      =\n* 1501 Certified\n* [[300 Entertainment|300]]\n* [[Warner Music Group|Warner]]\n| writer     =\n* [[Megan Thee Stallion|Megan Pete]]\n* [[J. White Did It|Anthony White]]\n* Bobby Session, Jr.\n| producer   = [[J. White Did It]]\n| prev_title = Freak\n| prev_year  = 2020\n| next_title = [[Savage (song)#Beyonc\u00e9 remix|Savage (Remix)]]\n| next_year  = 2020\n| misc       =\n}}\n\n\"'''Savage'''\" is a song by American rapper [[Megan Thee Stallion]]. It was released on March 6, 2020 as part of her EP ''[[Suga (EP)|Suga]]'' and later sent to US [[Contemporary hit radio|Top 40 radio]] formats on April 7, 2020 by 1501 Certified Entertainment and [[300 Entertainment]] as the third single from the EP.<ref name=\"AllAccess\">{{cite web|title=Top 40/M Future Releases|url=https://www.allaccess.com/top40-mainstream/future-releases|website=All Access|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200406195249/https://www.allaccess.com/top40-mainstream/future-releases|archivedate=April 6, 2020|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref> The song went viral on video-sharing app [[TikTok]], with people performing the \"Savage\" dance challenge during the song's chorus. A remix featuring [[Beyonc\u00e9]] was released on April 29, 2020.\n\n==Recording==\nAccording to [[audio engineer|engineer]], Eddie \"eMIX\" Hernandez, Megan did the song \"on the spot\", in under an hour. Hernandez explained the recording process: \"The collaboration was going on at the same time. We were building as the song was forming. While he [producer [[J. White Did It]]] was laying down the [[snare drum|snares]] and the [[bass drum|kicks]], she was writing to the skeleton of the beat. Once he had the production all ready and sent it over to me, she was ready to go. She had all her writing done. Her recording?\u00a0She knocks them things out\".<ref name=\"eMix\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.revolt.tv/platform/amp/2020/3/6/21168229/megan-thee-stallion-suga-engineer-emix-interview|title=Studio Sessions - eMIX talks working with Megan Thee Stallion on 'Suga,' JT recording before her prison stint, Rick Ross and more|work=[[Revolt (TV network)|Revolt]]|last=Nelson Jr|first=Keith|date=March 6, 2020|accessdate=March 30, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Composition==\nCandace McDuffie of ''[[Consequence of Sound]]'' noted, in the song, Megan \"paints herself as 'the [[ghetto|hood]] [[Mona Lisa]]' while celebrating her complexity\".<ref name=\"COS\" /> \nMegan employs huge bravado on the song, which, according to ''[[HipHopDX]]''{{'}}s Aaron McKrell, works to her advantage, as she \"surgically pummels a formidable [[J. White Did It]] beat into submission, and still makes time for cool quips like '''I need a mop to clean the floor, it's too much drip, ooh''{{'}}\".<ref name=\"HipHopDX\">{{Cite web|url=https://hiphopdx.com/reviews/id.3633/title.review-megan-thee-stallions-suga-fails-to-hit-the-sweet-spot|title=Review: Megan Thee Stallion's 'Suga' Fails To Hit The Sweet Spot|work=[[HipHopDX]]|last=McKrell|first=Aaron|date=March 23, 2020|accessdate=March 30, 2020}}</ref> [[Complex (magazine)|''Complex'']]'s Jessica McKinney said the beat is \"reminiscent of nostalgic hip-hop music videos set on a Miami beach, and its chorus is expressive, which is perfect for dancing\".<ref name=\"Complex\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/tiktok-songs-worth-listening-to/|title= 12 Songs Blowing Up on TikTok (That Are Actually Worth Listening to)|last=McKinney|first=Jessica|work=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]|date=March 26, 2020|accessdate=March 30, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\n''[[Consequence of Sound]]'' named \"Savage\" as one of the essential tracks off [[Suga (EP)|''Suga'']].<ref name=\"COS\">{{Cite web|url=https://consequenceofsound.net/2020/03/album-review-megan-thee-stallion-suga/|title=Megan Thee Stallion Hones Her Craft on the Suga EP|work=[[Consequence of Sound]]|last=McDuffie|first=Candace|date=March 10, 2020|accessdate=March 25, 2020}}</ref> [[Complex (magazine)|''Complex'']]'s Jessica McKinney also named it a \"stand-out track\" from the EP.<ref name=\"Complex\" /> ''[[New York\u00a0(magazine)#Digital expansion and destination sites|Vulture]]'' commented that the song was \"joyfully conceited\", and that previous single \"'B.I.T.C.H.' is a little lightweight as a first single when there's heat like 'Savage' on deck\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vulture.com/2020/03/megan-thee-stallon-suga-review-label-drama.html/|title=Why Shouldn't Megan Thee Stallion Take What's Hers?|work=Vulture|accessdate=March 25, 2020}}</ref> Rob Sheffield of ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' wrote that Megan is \"at her absolute peak\" and \"on top\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-album-reviews/megan-thee-stallion-suga-964567/|title=Megan Thee Stallion is at Her Peak on Suga|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|last=Sheffield|first=Rob|date=March 9, 2020|accessdate=March 29, 2020}}</ref> Following its release, ''[[The Fader]]''{{'}}s Salvatore Maicki named \"Savage\" one of the \"10 songs you need in your life this week\", saying Megan checks all of the boxes [classy, [[Bourgeoisie|bougie]],\u00a0ratchet, sassy, moody,\u00a0AND\u00a0nasty] and \"sounds [[Cool (aesthetic)|fly]] as fuck while doing it\".<ref name=\"TheFader\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.thefader.com/2020/03/12/new-songs-playlist-lil-uzi-megan-thee-stallion-yaeji-dixie-chicks/amp|title=10 songs you need in your life this week|work=[[The FADER]]|last=Maicki|first=Salvatore|date=March 12, 2020|accessdate=March 30, 2020}}</ref> [[Vice (magazine)|''Vice'']]'s Kristin Corry listed it as one of the best songs for the month of March 2020, asserting that \"with a [[hook (music)|hook]] that acknowledges all parts of her [Megan's] identity, just like each of her EPs introduces a new persona, it's no wonder the world fell in love with it\".<ref name=\"Vice\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.vice.com/en_us/article/pke4py/best-songs-march-2020|title=The 11 Songs We Couldn't Get Enough of This March|work=[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]]|last=Corry|first=Kristin|date=March 27, 2020|accessdate=March 30, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==TikTok challenge==\nThe \"Savage\" dance challenge was created by popular [[TikTok]] user Keara Wilson, whose viral clip racked up 15.7 million views and 2.4 million likes as of March 20, 2020.<ref name=\"Genius\">{{Cite web|url=https://genius.com/a/megan-thee-stallion-s-savage-looks-poised-to-be-her-next-hit-thanks-to-this-viral-tiktok-challenge/|title=Megan Thee Stallion's \"Savage\" Looks Poised To Be Her Next Hit Thanks To This Viral TikTok Challenge|website=[[Genius (website)|Genius]]|last=Fu|first=Eddie|accessdate=March 25, 2020}}</ref> Wilson posted her video for five days continuously, until it started going viral, and on March 16, Megan posted her own video, as well as videos of her fans and celebrities performing the challenge.<ref name=\"Oprah\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.oprahmag.com/entertainment/amp31932915/savage-challenge-megan-thee-stallion-lyrics/|title=Why You Can't Escape Megan Thee Stallion's \"Savage Challenge\" on TikTok|last=Jean-Phillipe|first=McKenzie|work=[[O, The Oprah Magazine|O magazine]]|date=March 25, 2020|accessdate=March 30, 2020}}</ref> The challenge involves people completing a \"quick and energetic\" choreographed dance.<ref name=\"Oprah\" />\n\n==Music video==\nA Gracie Rothey-created lyric video premiered on April 7, 2020. It sees an animated\u00a0Keara Wilson doing the famous [[TikTok]] dance she created, as the lyrics pass through on screen.<ref name=\"Lyric Vid\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.revolt.tv/platform/amp/new-music/2020/4/7/21212369/megan-thee-stallion-savage-lyric-video|title=Megan Thee Stallion reveals lyric visual for \"Savage\"|website=[[Revolt (TV network)|Revolt]]|last=Powell|first=Jon|date=April 7, 2020|accessdate=April 8, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2020)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{single chart|Billboardargentinahot100|95|artist=Megan Thee Stallion|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 30, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Australia ([[ARIA Charts|ARIA]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ariacharts.com.au/charts/singles-chart|title=ARIA Australian Top 50 Singles|publisher=[[Australian Recording Industry Association]]|date=April 20, 2020|accessdate=April 18, 2020}}</ref>\n| 14\n|-\n{{single chart|Austria|39|artist=Megan Thee Stallion|song=Savage|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Flanders|35|artist=Megan Thee Stallion|song=Savage|rowheader=true|accessdate=May 8, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Wallonia Tip|3|artist=Megan Thee Stallion|song=Savage|rowheader=true|accessdate=May 8, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Canada|16|artist=Megan Thee Stallion|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 14, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Czechdigital|25|year=2020|week=16|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 21, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Denmark ([[Tracklisten]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hitlisten.nu/default.asp?w=16&y=2020&list=t40|title=Track Top-40 Uge 16, 2020|publisher=[[Hitlisten]]|accessdate=April 29, 2020}}</ref>\n| 36\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Estonia ([[Eesti Tipp-40]])<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ekspress.delfi.ee/areen/eesti-tipp-40-muusikas-sel-nadalal-paugutab-tradattack?id=89544845|title=Eesti Tipp-40 Muusikas: Sel n\u00e4dalal paugutab Trad.Attack!|language=Estonian|last=Nestor|first=Siim|website=[[Eesti Ekspress]]|date=April 14, 2020|accessdate=April 14, 2020}}</ref>\