lt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Megan Thee Stallion]] featuring [[Beyonc\u00e9]]\n| album      =\n| released   = April 29, 2020\n| format     =\n* [[Music download|Digital download]]\n| recorded   = \n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = <!-- Please source genres -->\n| length     =\n* {{duration|m=4|s=02}}\n| label      =\n* 1501 Certified\n* [[300 Entertainment|300]]\n* [[Warner Music Group|Warner]]\n| writer     =\n* [[Beyonc\u00e9 Knowles-Carter]]\n* [[Megan Thee Stallion|Megan Pete]]\n* [[J. White Did It|Anthony White]]\n* Bobby Session, Jr.\n* Derrick Milano\n* [[The-Dream|Terius Youngdell Nash]]\n* [[Pardison Fontaine|Jordan Kyle Lanier Thorpe]]\n* [[Jay-Z|Shawn Corey Carter]]\n* [[Starrah|Brittany Starrah Hazzard]]\n| producer   = [[J. White Did It]]\n| chronology = [[Megan Thee Stallion]]\n| prev_title = Savage\n| prev_year  = 2020\n| next_title = \n| next_year  = \n| misc       = {{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[Beyonc\u00e9]]\n | type       = single\n | prev_title = [[Brown Skin Girl]]\n | prev_year  = 2019\n | title      = Savage (Remix)\n | year       = 2020\n | next_title = \n | next_year  = \n}}\n{{External music video|1={{YouTube|lEIqjoO0-Bs|\"Savage Remix\"}}|header=Audio video|type=single}}\n}}\nOn April 29, 2020, a remix featuring [[Beyonc\u00e9]] was released.<ref name=\"RapUpRemix\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.rap-up.com/2020/04/29/beyonce-megan-thee-stallion-savage-remix/|title=Megan Thee Stallion Releases Savage Remix featuring Beyonc\u00e9|work=[[Rap-Up]]|date=April 29, 2020|accessdate=April 29, 2020}}</ref> All proceeds benefit Bread of Life Houston's [[COVID-19]] relief efforts, which includes providing over 14 tons of food and supplies to 500 families and 100 senior citizens in [[Houston]] weekly.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Beyonc\u00e9, Megan Thee Stallion Drop \u2018Savage\u2019 Remix For Houston Coronavirus Relief|url=https://www.ibtimes.com/beyonce-megan-thee-stallion-drop-savage-remix-houston-coronavirus-relief-2967423|last=Armecin|first=Catherine|date=2020-04-30|website=International Business Times|accessdate=2020-05-04}}</ref> New TikTok challenges were made for the song, including by the original \"Savage\" dance challenge creator, Keara Wilson.<ref>{{Cite web|title=The \"Savage\" Challenge Has Already Been Updated Hours After Megan Thee Stallion Dropped The Remix With Beyonc\u00e9|url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/adeonibada/beyonce-megan-thee-stallion-savage-challenge-remix-tiktok|last=Onibada|first=Ade|website=BuzzFeed|language=en|accessdate=2020-05-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title='Savage Remix' Inspires Some Equally Savage Choreography|url=https://www.theroot.com/savage-remix-inspires-some-equally-savage-choreography-1843226224|website=The Root|language=en-us|accessdate=2020-05-04}}</ref>\n===Critical reception===\n''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]'' named \"Savage (Remix)\" Best New Track, stating that \"Beyonc\u00e9 upgrades the original from a good song to a multi-dimensional one\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/tracks/megan-thee-stallion-savage-remix-ft-beyonce/|title=Listen to \"Savage Remix\" [ft. Beyonc\u00e9] by Megan Thee Stallion|via=pitchfork.com}}</ref> Craig Jenkins for [[Vulture magazine|''Vulture'']] wrote that Beyonc\u00e9 and Megan \"brought back the lost art of a killer remix\", adding that \"it's so rare in this era for a remix to feel like an event and not just a few new words plopped onto an existing song\".<ref>{{Cite web|title=Beyonc\u00e9 and Megan Thee Stallion Just Brought Back the Lost Art of a Killer Remix|url=https://www.vulture.com/2020/04/beyonce-megan-thee-stallion-savage-remix-song-review.html|last=Jenkins|first=Craig|date=2020-04-29|website=Vulture|language=en-us|accessdate=2020-05-04}}</ref> [[Jon Caramanica]] for ''[[The New York Times]]'' described the track as \"fantastic, far more involved and intricate than most blink-and-you'll-miss-it collaborations\".<ref>{{Cite news|last=Pareles|first=Jon|last2=Caramanica|first2=Jon|last3=Russonello|first3=Giovanni|date=2020-05-01|title=Beyonc\u00e9 Amps Up 'Savage,' and 12 More New Songs|language=en-US|work=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/05/01/arts/music/playlist-beyonce-megan-thee-stallion-oasis.html|accessdate=2020-05-04|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> Jael Goldfine from ''[[Paper (magazine)|Paper]]'' declared the song \"a perfect reminder that Beyonc\u00e9 is a gifted rapper, whether taking control or backing Meg up with sexy little 'Okay-okays', and 'them jeans, them jeans'\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.papermag.com/beyonce-megan-thee-stallion-savage-remix-2645876590.html?rebelltitem=7#rebelltitem7?rebelltitem=7|title=Today Is About Beyonc\u00e9|date=April 29, 2020|website=PAPER}}</ref>  Brittany Spanos from ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' wrote the song \"feels like it was always meant to be a duet between the pair, with Beyonc\u00e9 offering up multiple verses as well as some vocal runs that seamlessly blend with the smooth beat\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/beyonce-megan-thee-stallion-savage-remix-991603/|title=Beyonc\u00e9 Flexes on Remix of Megan Thee Stallion's 'Savage'|first=Brittany|last=Spanos|date=April 29, 2020}}</ref> \n\nWriting for ''[[GQ]]'', Max Cea called the pairing \"a natural fit\" whose \"styles complement each others': Beyonc\u00e9's breathy flutterings punctuate Megan's gusto; Megan's snappy choruses act as a sturdy platform for Beyonc\u00e9's various modes (singing, rapping, growling, seductively whispering).\"<ref>{{Cite web|title=Beyonc\u00e9 Emerges from Self-Isolation to Remind You That She's a \"Savage\"|url=https://www.gq.com/story/beyonce-megan-thee-stallion-savage-remix|last=Cea|first=Max|website=GQ|language=en|accessdate=2020-05-04}}</ref> Kiana Fitzgerald for ''[[Texas Monthly]]'' praised the remix as a track that \"pairs Megan's insuppressible, ebullient energy with Beyonc\u00e9's perfectionist work ethic, and benefits their shared hometown of Houston\", where \"Megan, an upstart MC, and Beyonc\u00e9, a cemented veteran, came together as artists from south Houston to represent something greater: the fact that they're fully realized women, with lives that mirror those of their listeners despite the difference in their respective lifestyles.\"<ref>{{Cite web|title=Megan Thee Stallion and Beyonc\u00e9\u2019s Electrifyingly Fun \u2018Savage\u2019 Remix Is for Texans, by Texans|url=https://www.texasmonthly.com/the-culture/megan-thee-stallion-beyonce-savage-remix-houston-texas/|date=2020-04-30|website=Texas Monthly|language=en|accessdate=2020-05-04}}</ref>\n\n=== Impact ===\n[[Houston mayor|Houston Mayor]] [[Sylvester Turner]] announced that both Megan and Beyonc\u00e9 will receive their own day in Houston, with Turner acknowledging \"both artists' contributions to uplifting our communities, holding down H-Town, & for helping us remain Houston Strong\".<ref>{{Cite web|title=Houston's Megan Thee Stallion and Beyonc\u00e9 to receive their own day in Houston|url=https://kblx.com/entertainment-news/houstons-megan-thee-stallion-and-beyonc-to-receive-their-own-day-in-houston/|last=Group|first=Music News|date=2020-05-01|website=102.9 KBLX|language=en-US|accessdate=2020-05-04}}</ref> In addition to the proceeds from the remix being donated to Bread of Life Houston's COVID-19 relief efforts, the charity has also seen a significant boost in donations, with over 500 new donors in the first 24 hours after the song's release.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Beyonce And Megan Thee Stallion\u2019s \u2019Savage\u2019 Remix Boosts Charity Donations|url=https://uproxx.com/music/beyonce-megan-thee-stallion-savage-remix-charity/|date=2020-05-01|website=UPROXX|language=en-US|accessdate=2020-05-04}}</ref> \n\nThe [[Subscription service|subscription content service]] [[OnlyFans]], which Beyonc\u00e9 referenced in the remix, saw a 15% spike in traffic after the track's release.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Stern|first=Marlow|date=2020-04-30|title=Beyonc\u00e9 Gives Adult Site OnlyFans Big Bump With \u2018Savage\u2019 Remix Shout-Out|language=en|work=The Daily Beast|url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/adult-site-onlyfans-experiences-big-beyonce-bump-following-savage-remix|accessdate=2020-05-04}}</ref>\n\n[[Virginia]]-based dancer Morgan Bullock went viral for performing [[Irish stepdance]] to the remix. Despite receiving [[Racism|racist]] abuse due to Bullock being a black woman, Bullock received praise and support from admirers including [[Riverdance]] creator [[Bill Whelan]] and Beyonc\u00e9's mother [[Tina Knowles]], and was invited to perform in [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]] by [[Taoiseach]] [[Leo Varadkar]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=US Irish dancer Morgan Bullock talks about racism she faced after viral video success|url=https://www.irishexaminer.com/breakingnews/lifestyle/culture/us-irish-dancer-morgan-bullock-talks-about-racism-she-faced-after-viral-video-success-997922.html|last=Wednesday|last2=May 06|date=2020-05-06|website=www.irishexaminer.com|language=en|accessdate=2020-05-07|last3=Am|first3=2020-11:35}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2020-05-05|title=American Irish dancer speaks out after racist abuse|url=https://www.rte.ie/news/2020/0505/1136602-american-irish-dancer-speaks-out-after-racist-abuse/|language=en}}</ref>\n\nCaitlin Kelley for ''[[Forbes]]'' opined that the remix sets the precedent for \"the dawn of TikTok remixes\" and \"reinforces the app's hold on the charts\".<ref>{{Cite web|title=The Dawn Of TikTok Remixes Is Here Thanks To Beyonc\u00e9 And Nicki Minaj|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/caitlinkelley/2020/04/29/the-dawn-of-tiktok-remixes-is-here-thanks-to-beyonc-and-nicki-minaj/|last=Kelley|first=Caitlin|website=Forbes|language=en|accessdate=2020-05-04}}</ref>\n\n==Release history==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n! scope=\"col\"| Region\n! scope=\"col\"| Date\n! scope=\"col\"| Format\n! scope=\"col\"| Version\n! scope=\"col\"| Label\n! scope=\"col\"| {{abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| United States\n| April 7, 2020\n| [[Contemporary hit radio]]\n| Original\n| rowspan=\"4\"| {{hlist|1501 Certified|[[300 Entertainment|300]]|[[Warner Music Group|Warner]]}}\n|<ref name=\"AllAccess\" />\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Various\n| April 29, 2020\n| {{hlist|[[Music download|Digital download]]|[[Streaming media|streaming]]}}\n| rowspan=\"3\"| Remix featuring [[Beyonc\u00e9]]\n| <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/savage-remix-feat-beyonc\u00e9-single/1510814138|title=Savage Remix (feat. Beyonc\u00e9) - Single by Megan Thee Stallion on Apple Music|author=[[Megan Thee Stallion]]|date=April 29, 2020|website=music.apple.com}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"2\"| United Kingdom\n| rowspan=\"2\"| May 8, 2020\n| Contemporary hit radio\n| <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/articles/3tqPdBWF9yMbTrfjWvfKV8t/radio-1-playlist|title=BBC - Radio 1 Playlist|date=May 8, 2020|website=[[BBC Online|bbc.co.uk]]}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Urban contemporary]]\n| <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/articles/2sgpCPqVPgjqC7tHBb97kd9/the-1xtra-playlist|title=BBC - The 1Xtra Playlist|date=May 8, 2020|website=[[BBC Online|bbc.co.uk]]}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Megan Thee Stallion}}\n{{Beyonc\u00e9 songs}}\n\n[[Category:Megan Thee Stallion songs]]\n[[Category:2020 singles]]\n[[Category:2020 songs]]\n[[Category:Beyonc\u00e9 songs]]\n[[Category:TikTok songs]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by J. White Did It]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = Savage\n| type       = single\n| cover      = Megan Thee Stallion featuring Major Lazer - Savage (Remix).png\n| caption    = [[Major Lazer]] remix artwork\n| alt        =\n| artist     = [[Megan Thee Stallion]]\n| EP         = [[Suga (EP)|Suga]]\n| released   = April 7, 2020\n| format     =\n* [[Music download|Digital download]]\n* [[Streaming media|streaming]]\n| recorded   =\n| genre      = \n| length     = {{duration|m=2|s=35}}\n| label      =\n* 1501 Certified\n* [[300 Entertainment|300]]\n* [[Warner Music Group|Warner]]\n| writer     =\n* [[Megan Thee Stallion|Megan Pete]]\n* [[J. White Did It|Anthony White]]\n* Bobby Session, Jr.\n| producer   = [[J. White Did It]]\n| prev_title = Freak\n| prev_year  = 2020\n| next_title = [[Savage (song)#Beyonc\u00e9 remix|Savage (Remix)]]\n| next_year  = 2020\n| misc       =\n}}\n\n\"'''Savage'''\" is a song by American rapper [[Megan Thee Stallion]]. It was released on March 6, 2020 as part of her EP ''[[Suga (EP)|Suga]]'' and later sent to US [[Contemporary hit radio|Top 40 radio]] formats on April 7, 2020 by 1501 Certified Entertainment and [[300 Entertainment]] as the third single from the EP.<ref name=\"AllAccess\">{{cite web|title=Top 40/M Future Releases|url=https://www.allaccess.com/top40-mainstream/future-releases|website=All Access|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200406195249/https://www.allaccess.com/top40-mainstream/future-releases|archivedate=April 6, 2020|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref> The song went viral on video-sharing app [[TikTok]], with people performing the \"Savage\" dance challenge during the song's chorus. A remix featuring [[Beyonc\u00e9]] was released on April 29, 2020.\n\n==Recording==\nAccording to [[audio engineer|engineer]], Eddie \"eMIX\" Hernandez, Megan did the song \"on the spot\", in under an hour. Hernandez explained the recording process: \"The collaboration was going on at the same time. We were building as the song was forming. While he [producer [[J. White Did It]]] was laying down the [[snare drum|snares]] and the [[bass drum|kicks]], she was writing to the skeleton of the beat. Once he had the production all ready and sent it over to me, she was ready to go. She had all her writing done. Her recording?\u00a0She knocks them things out\".<ref name=\"eMix\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.revolt.tv/platform/amp/2020/3/6/21168229/megan-thee-stallion-suga-engineer-emix-interview|title=Studio Sessions - eMIX talks working with Megan Thee Stallion on 'Suga,' JT recording before her prison stint, Rick Ross and more|work=[[Revolt (TV network)|Revolt]]|last=Nelson Jr|first=Keith|date=March 6, 2020|accessdate=March 30, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Composition==\nCandace McDuffie of ''[[Consequence of Sound]]'' noted, in the song, Megan \"paints herself as 'the [[ghetto|hood]] [[Mona Lisa]]' while celebrating her complexity\".<ref name=\"COS\" /> \nMegan employs huge bravado on the song, which, according to ''[[HipHopDX]]''{{'}}s Aaron McKrell, works to her advantage, as she \"surgically pummels a formidable [[J. White Did It]] beat into submission, and still makes time for cool quips like '''I need a mop to clean the floor, it's too much drip, ooh''{{'}}\".<ref name=\"HipHopDX\">{{Cite web|url=https://hiphopdx.com/reviews/id.3633/title.review-megan-thee-stallions-suga-fails-to-hit-the-sweet-spot|title=Review: Megan Thee Stallion's 'Suga' Fails To Hit The Sweet Spot|work=[[HipHopDX]]|last=McKrell|first=Aaron|date=March 23, 2020|accessdate=March 30, 2020}}</ref> [[Complex (magazine)|''Complex'']]'s Jessica McKinney said the beat is \"reminiscent of nostalgic hip-hop music videos set on a Miami beach, and its chorus is expressive, which is perfect for dancing\".<ref name=\"Complex\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/tiktok-songs-worth-listening-to/|title= 12 Songs Blowing Up on TikTok (That Are Actually Worth Listening to)|last=McKinney|first=Jessica|work=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]|date=March 26, 2020|accessdate=March 30, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\n''[[Consequence of Sound]]'' named \"Savage\" as one of the essential tracks off [[Suga (EP)|''Suga'']].<ref name=\"COS\">{{Cite web|url=https://consequenceofsound.net/2020/03/album-review-megan-thee-stallion-suga/|title=Megan Thee Stallion Hones Her Craft on the Suga EP|work=[[Consequence of Sound]]|last=McDuffie|first=Candace|date=March 10, 2020|accessdate=March 25, 2020}}</ref> [[Complex (magazine)|''Complex'']]'s Jessica McKinney also named it a \"stand-out track\" from the EP.<ref name=\"Complex\" /> ''[[New York\u00a0(magazine)#Digital expansion and destination sites|Vulture]]'' commented that the song was \"joyfully conceited\", and that previous single \"'B.I.T.C.H.' is a little lightweight as a first single when there's heat like 'Savage' on deck\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vulture.com/2020/03/megan-thee-stallon-suga-review-label-drama.html/|title=Why Shouldn't Megan Thee Stallion Take What's Hers?|work=Vulture|accessdate=March 25, 2020}}</ref> Rob Sheffield of ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' wrote that Megan is \"at her absolute peak\" and \"on top\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-album-reviews/megan-thee-stallion-suga-964567/|title=Megan Thee Stallion is at Her Peak on Suga|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|last=Sheffield|first=Rob|date=March 9, 2020|accessdate=March 29, 2020}}</ref> Following its release, ''[[The Fader]]''{{'}}s Salvatore Maicki named \"Savage\" one of the \"10 songs you need in your life this week\", saying Megan checks all of the boxes [classy, [[Bourgeoisie|bougie]],\u00a0ratchet, sassy, moody,\u00a0AND\u00a0nasty] and \"sounds [[Cool (aesthetic)|fly]] as fuck while doing it\".<ref name=\"TheFader\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.thefader.com/2020/03/12/new-songs-playlist-lil-uzi-megan-thee-stallion-yaeji-dixie-chicks/amp|title=10 songs you need in your life this week|work=[[The FADER]]|last=Maicki|first=Salvatore|date=March 12, 2020|accessdate=March 30, 2020}}</ref> [[Vice (magazine)|''Vice'']]'s Kristin Corry listed it as one of the best songs for the month of March 2020, asserting that \"with a [[hook (music)|hook]] that acknowledges all parts of her [Megan's] identity, just like each of her EPs introduces a new persona, it's no wonder the world fell in love with it\".<ref name=\"Vice\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.vice.com/en_us/article/pke4py/best-songs-march-2020|title=The 11 Songs We Couldn't Get Enough of This March|work=[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]]|last=Corry|first=Kristin|date=March 27, 2020|accessdate=March 30, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==TikTok challenge==\nThe \"Savage\" dance challenge was created by popular [[TikTok]] user Keara Wilson, whose viral clip racked up 15.7 million views and 2.4 million likes as of March 20, 2020.<ref name=\"Genius\">{{Cite web|url=https://genius.com/a/megan-thee-stallion-s-savage-looks-poised-to-be-her-next-hit-thanks-to-this-viral-tiktok-challenge/|title=Megan Thee Stallion's \"Savage\" Looks Poised To Be Her Next Hit Thanks To This Viral TikTok Challenge|website=[[Genius (website)|Genius]]|last=Fu|first=Eddie|accessdate=March 25, 2020}}</ref> Wilson posted her video for five days continuously, until it started going viral, and on March 16, Megan posted her own video, as well as videos of her fans and celebrities performing the challenge.<ref name=\"Oprah\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.oprahmag.com/entertainment/amp31932915/savage-challenge-megan-thee-stallion-lyrics/|title=Why You Can't Escape Megan Thee Stallion's \"Savage Challenge\" on TikTok|last=Jean-Phillipe|first=McKenzie|work=[[O, The Oprah Magazine|O magazine]]|date=March 25, 2020|accessdate=March 30, 2020}}</ref> The challenge involves people completing a \"quick and energetic\" choreographed dance.<ref name=\"Oprah\" />\n\n==Music video==\nA Gracie Rothey-created lyric video premiered on April 7, 2020. It sees an animated\u00a0Keara Wilson doing the famous [[TikTok]] dance she created, as the lyrics pass through on screen.<ref name=\"Lyric Vid\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.revolt.tv/platform/amp/new-music/2020/4/7/21212369/megan-thee-stallion-savage-lyric-video|title=Megan Thee Stallion reveals lyric visual for \"Savage\"|website=[[Revolt (TV network)|Revolt]]|last=Powell|first=Jon|date=April 7, 2020|accessdate=April 8, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2020)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{single chart|Billboardargentinahot100