te Did It|Anthony White]]\n* Bobby Session, Jr.\n* Derrick Milano\n* [[The-Dream|Terius Youngdell Nash]]\n* [[Pardison Fontaine|Jordan Kyle Lanier Thorpe]]\n* [[Jay-Z|Shawn Corey Carter]]\n* [[Starrah|Brittany Starrah Hazzard]]\n| producer   = [[J. White Did It]]\n| chronology = [[Megan Thee Stallion]]\n| prev_title = Savage\n| prev_year  = 2020\n| next_title = \n| next_year  = \n| misc       = {{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[Beyonc\u00e9]]\n | type       = single\n | prev_title = [[Brown Skin Girl]]\n | prev_year  = 2019\n | title      = Savage (Remix)\n | year       = 2020\n | next_title = \n | next_year  = \n}}\n{{External music video|1={{YouTube|lEIqjoO0-Bs|\"Savage Remix\"}}|header=Audio video|type=single}}\n}}\nOn April 29, 2020, a remix featuring [[Beyonc\u00e9]] was released.<ref name=\"RapUpRemix\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.rap-up.com/2020/04/29/beyonce-megan-thee-stallion-savage-remix/|title=Megan Thee Stallion Releases Savage Remix featuring Beyonc\u00e9|work=[[Rap-Up]]|date=April 29, 2020|accessdate=April 29, 2020}}</ref> All proceeds benefit Bread of Life Houston's [[COVID-19]] relief efforts, which includes providing over 14 tons of food and supplies to 500 families and 100 senior citizens in [[Houston]] weekly.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Beyonc\u00e9, Megan Thee Stallion Drop \u2018Savage\u2019 Remix For Houston Coronavirus Relief|url=https://www.ibtimes.com/beyonce-megan-thee-stallion-drop-savage-remix-houston-coronavirus-relief-2967423|last=Armecin|first=Catherine|date=2020-04-30|website=International Business Times|accessdate=2020-05-04}}</ref> New TikTok challenges were made for the song, including by the original \"Savage\" dance challenge creator, Keara Wilson.<ref>{{Cite web|title=The \"Savage\" Challenge Has Already Been Updated Hours After Megan Thee Stallion Dropped The Remix With Beyonc\u00e9|url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/adeonibada/beyonce-megan-thee-stallion-savage-challenge-remix-tiktok|last=Onibada|first=Ade|website=BuzzFeed|language=en|accessdate=2020-05-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title='Savage Remix' Inspires Some Equally Savage Choreography|url=https://www.theroot.com/savage-remix-inspires-some-equally-savage-choreography-1843226224|website=The Root|language=en-us|accessdate=2020-05-04}}</ref>\n===Critical reception===\n''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]'' named \"Savage (Remix)\" Best New Track, stating that \"Beyonc\u00e9 upgrades the original from a good song to a multi-dimensional one\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/tracks/megan-thee-stallion-savage-remix-ft-beyonce/|title=Listen to \"Savage Remix\" [ft. Beyonc\u00e9] by Megan Thee Stallion|via=pitchfork.com}}</ref> Craig Jenkins for [[Vulture magazine|''Vulture'']] wrote that Beyonc\u00e9 and Megan \"brought back the lost art of a killer remix\", adding that \"it's so rare in this era for a remix to feel like an event and not just a few new words plopped onto an existing song\".<ref>{{Cite web|title=Beyonc\u00e9 and Megan Thee Stallion Just Brought Back the Lost Art of a Killer Remix|url=https://www.vulture.com/2020/04/beyonce-megan-thee-stallion-savage-remix-song-review.html|last=Jenkins|first=Craig|date=2020-04-29|website=Vulture|language=en-us|accessdate=2020-05-04}}</ref> [[Jon Caramanica]] for ''[[The New York Times]]'' described the track as \"fantastic, far more involved and intricate than most blink-and-you'll-miss-it collaborations\".<ref>{{Cite news|last=Pareles|first=Jon|last2=Caramanica|first2=Jon|last3=Russonello|first3=Giovanni|date=2020-05-01|title=Beyonc\u00e9 Amps Up 'Savage,' and 12 More New Songs|language=en-US|work=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/05/01/arts/music/playlist-beyonce-megan-thee-stallion-oasis.html|accessdate=2020-05-04|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> Jael Goldfine from ''[[Paper (magazine)|Paper]]'' declared the song \"a perfect reminder that Beyonc\u00e9 is a gifted rapper, whether taking control or backing Meg up with sexy little 'Okay-okays', and 'them jeans, them jeans'\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.papermag.com/beyonce-megan-thee-stallion-savage-remix-2645876590.html?rebelltitem=7#rebelltitem7?rebelltitem=7|title=Today Is About Beyonc\u00e9|date=April 29, 2020|website=PAPER}}</ref>  Brittany Spanos from ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' wrote the song \"feels like it was always meant to be a duet between the pair, with Beyonc\u00e9 offering up multiple verses as well as some vocal runs that seamlessly blend with the smooth beat\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/beyonce-megan-thee-stallion-savage-remix-991603/|title=Beyonc\u00e9 Flexes on Remix of Megan Thee Stallion's 'Savage'|first=Brittany|last=Spanos|date=April 29, 2020}}</ref> \n\nWriting for ''[[GQ]]'', Max Cea called the pairing \"a natural fit\" whose \"styles complement each others': Beyonc\u00e9's breathy flutterings punctuate Megan's gusto; Megan's snappy choruses act as a sturdy platform for Beyonc\u00e9's various modes (singing, rapping, growling, seductively whispering).\"<ref>{{Cite web|title=Beyonc\u00e9 Emerges from Self-Isolation to Remind You That She's a \"Savage\"|url=https://www.gq.com/story/beyonce-megan-thee-stallion-savage-remix|last=Cea|first=Max|website=GQ|language=en|accessdate=2020-05-04}}</ref> Kiana Fitzgerald for ''[[Texas Monthly]]'' praised the remix as a track that \"pairs Megan's insuppressible, ebullient energy with Beyonc\u00e9's perfectionist work ethic, and benefits their shared hometown of Houston\", where \"Megan, an upstart MC, and Beyonc\u00e9, a cemented veteran, came together as artists from south Houston to represent something greater: the fact that they're fully realized women, with lives that mirror those of their listeners despite the difference in their respective lifestyles.\"<ref>{{Cite web|title=Megan Thee Stallion and Beyonc\u00e9\u2019s Electrifyingly Fun \u2018Savage\u2019 Remix Is for Texans, by Texans|url=https://www.texasmonthly.com/the-culture/megan-thee-stallion-beyonce-savage-remix-houston-texas/|date=2020-04-30|website=Texas Monthly|language=en|accessdate=2020-05-04}}</ref>\n\n=== Impact ===\n[[Houston mayor|Houston Mayor]] [[Sylvester Turner]] announced that both Megan and Beyonc\u00e9 will receive their own day in Houston, with Turner acknowledging \"both artists' contributions to uplifting our communities, holding down H-Town, & for helping us remain Houston Strong\".<ref>{{Cite web|title=Houston's Megan Thee Stallion and Beyonc\u00e9 to receive their own day in Houston|url=https://kblx.com/entertainment-news/houstons-megan-thee-stallion-and-beyonc-to-receive-their-own-day-in-houston/|last=Group|first=Music News|date=2020-05-01|website=102.9 KBLX|language=en-US|accessdate=2020-05-04}}</ref> In addition to the proceeds from the remix being donated to Bread of Life Houston's COVID-19 relief efforts, the charity has also seen a significant boost in donations, with over 500 new donors in the first 24 hours after the song's release.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Beyonce And Megan Thee Stallion\u2019s \u2019Savage\u2019 Remix Boosts Charity Donations|url=https://uproxx.com/music/beyonce-megan-thee-stallion-savage-remix-charity/|date=2020-05-01|website=UPROXX|language=en-US|accessdate=2020-05-04}}</ref> \n\nThe [[Subscription service|subscription content service]] [[OnlyFans]], which Beyonc\u00e9 referenced in the remix, saw a 15% spike in traffic after the track's release.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Stern|first=Marlow|date=2020-04-30|title=Beyonc\u00e9 Gives Adult Site OnlyFans Big Bump With \u2018Savage\u2019 Remix Shout-Out|language=en|work=The Daily Beast|url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/adult-site-onlyfans-experiences-big-beyonce-bump-following-savage-remix|accessdate=2020-05-04}}</ref>\n\n[[Virginia]]-based dancer Morgan Bullock went viral for performing [[Irish stepdance]] to the remix. Despite receiving [[Racism|racist]] abuse due to Bullock being a black woman, Bullock received praise and support from admirers including [[Riverdance]] creator [[Bill Whelan]] and Beyonc\u00e9's mother [[Tina Knowles]], and was invited to perform in [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]] by [[Taoiseach]] [[Leo Varadkar]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=US Irish dancer Morgan Bullock talks about racism she faced after viral video success|url=https://www.irishexaminer.com/breakingnews/lifestyle/culture/us-irish-dancer-morgan-bullock-talks-about-racism-she-faced-after-viral-video-success-997922.html|last=Wednesday|last2=May 06|date=2020-05-06|website=www.irishexaminer.com|language=en|accessdate=2020-05-07|last3=Am|first3=2020-11:35}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2020-05-05|title=American Irish dancer speaks out after racist abuse|url=https://www.rte.ie/news/2020/0505/1136602-american-irish-dancer-speaks-out-after-racist-abuse/|language=en}}</ref>\n\nCaitlin Kelley for ''[[Forbes]]'' opined that the remix sets the precedent for \"the dawn of TikTok remixes\" and \"reinforces the app's hold on the charts\".<ref>{{Cite web|title=The Dawn Of TikTok Remixes Is Here Thanks To Beyonc\u00e9 And Nicki Minaj|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/caitlinkelley/2020/04/29/the-dawn-of-tiktok-remixes-is-here-thanks-to-beyonc-and-nicki-minaj/|last=Kelley|first=Caitlin|website=Forbes|language=en|accessdate=2020-05-04}}</ref>\n\n==Release history==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n! scope=\"col\"| Region\n! scope=\"col\"| Date\n! scope=\"col\"| Format\n! scope=\"col\"| Version\n! scope=\"col\"| Label\n! scope=\"col\"| {{abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| United States\n| April 7, 2020\n| [[Contemporary hit radio]]\n| Original\n| rowspan=\"4\"| {{hlist|1501 Certified|[[300 Entertainment|300]]|[[Warner Music Group|Warner]]}}\n|<ref name=\"AllAccess\" />\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Various\n| April 29, 2020\n| {{hlist|[[Music download|Digital download]]|[[Streaming media|streaming]]}}\n| rowspan=\"3\"| Remix featuring [[Beyonc\u00e9]]\n| <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/savage-remix-feat-beyonc\u00e9-single/1510814138|title=Savage Remix (feat. Beyonc\u00e9) - 